file.comment: intro:Foster: "The old man was trying to tell the future. Looking for pictures in the campfire..."
intro:Shaman: "Evil born deep beneath the city... far from the light of day."
intro:Shaman: "I see it growing, safe beneath a sky of steel..."
intro:Shaman: "Scheming in the dark... gathering strength."
intro:Shaman: "And now... ohhh.... now the evil spreads..."
intro:Shaman: "It sends deadly feelers over the land above..."
intro:Shaman: "Across the gap... reaching towards this very place!"
intro:Foster: "I'd seen him do this a hundred times, but I humoured him."
intro:Foster: "After all, he'd been like a father to me."
intro:Foster: "And what does this evil want here?"
intro:Shaman: "I fear the evil wants you!"
intro:Foster: "That was when Joey piped up..."
intro:Joey: "Foster! Sensors detect incoming audio source!"
intro:Shaman: "The evil! The evil is nearly here...!"
intro:Foster: "It sounded more like a 'copter than a demon."
intro:Foster: "But next thing, all hell let loose anyway..."
intro:Shaman: "Run, Foster! Run! Hide from the evil!"
intro:Joey: "Better make my next body move faster, Foster..."
intro:Foster: "He was only a robot, but, well, I loved the little guy."
intro:Foster: "Then, as suddenly as it started, the shooting stopped."
intro:Foster: "There was a moment's silence as the copter cut its rotors, then..."
intro:Reich: "Whoever is in charge here, come forward..."
intro:Foster: "Only a fool would have argued with that firepower."
intro:Shaman: "... I am the leader of these people... We are peaceful..."
intro:Reich: "Who wasn't born in this garbage dump..."
intro:Reich: "Who came from the city as a child..."
intro:Reich: "We want to take him home again."
intro:Foster: "My mind racing, I remembered where I'd seen that symbol before..."
intro:Foster: "It was the day the tribe found me..."
intro:Shaman: "Hah! Welcome to the Gap, Robert!"
intro:Foster: "As he patched me up, the old man had gently explained that there was no way back into the City..."
intro:Foster: "And I already knew there was nothing he could do for mother."
intro:Foster: "His tribe was poor, but they treated me like one of their own..."
intro:Foster: "I learned how to survive in the wasteland they called the Gap..."
intro:Foster: "And scavenging from the City dumps."
intro:Foster: "As the years passed, I forgot my life in the City."
intro:Joey: "I'm your (zzzt) friend... call me (zzzt) Joey."
intro:Shaman: "This is what we'll call you now you've come of age, son."
intro:Shaman: "We found you... we fostered you..."
intro:Shaman: "So that makes you Robert Foster."
intro:Reich: "Give us the runaway or we'll shoot everyone..."
intro:Foster: "The old man had been right, for once..."
intro:Shaman: "No, my son! Don't let the evil take you! Run!"
intro:Guard: "DNA scan confirms it's him, sir."
intro:Foster: "Evil had come to the Gap, just as he said."
intro:Foster: "But had the old man seen why it wanted me?"
intro:Foster: "Or what it would do next?"
intro:Foster: "It was too late to ask him now."
intro:Foster: "All I could do was wait."
intro:Foster: "Just like on a hunt. Just like the old man taught me."
intro:Foster: "It was dawn when we reached the City."
intro:Reich: "Land in the central Security compound."
intro:Foster: "A dawn my tribe would never see."
intro:Foster: "They were no more than a note in Reich's book now."
intro:Guard: "Yes, sir. Locking on automatic landing beacon."
intro:Foster: "But what was I? Why did..."
intro:Guard: "Sir! The guidance system! It's gone crazy!"
intro:Foster: "Maybe I'd get some answers now."
